social_posts.post_text:
So incredibly grateful to make the @brides Best Photographers list again, along with so many of my insanely talented friends! It’s wild to imagine that over time, all the small steps you take toward your dreams as a small business owner can make dreams come true. 
When I took the leap to go full time photographing weddings, I was a terrified single mom, with a mortgage, doubt, the entire nine yards. I had no idea how much I could truly love this industry. I’m so grateful to all my amazing clients, the planners that trust me, and this community that is endlessly encouraging and creative. Because of you, I’ve been able to build a life, and show my son he can chase his dreams and find success and happiness. 
During this journey, I married and had a baby, all while still capturing memories for my clients all over the world. And this year, I got to add to my team with the amazing @jenneferwilson & @alisonheffington. Showcasing love stories from all different cultures, skintones, orientations, destinations, is such an honor. Being named to the @brides list is an amazing feeling. Named Top 50 in the country is wild, and I’m forever grateful! Thank you so much @brides @shelbywax @gabbadabbadooo.
.

The backdrop for @sar_schreiber, editor of Martha Stewart weddings, and @zachvw92’s spring wedding was the iconic Abbey mansion in Cape May, N.J. a Gothic Revival estate built in 1869. The couple met for their first look on the Abbey’s side porch, where hanging ferns and architectural woodwork set an intimate scene. “Walking out onto the porch, and passing through that arched doorway, felt like I was taking a step backwards in time-but it was also a step forward, towards our future,” says Sarah.
See more from Sarah and Zach’s “Victorian garden picnic by the sea.” 
We will never tire of this beautiful day! Our favorite weddings are intimate, full of intention and allow our clients personalities to shine! Thrilled to see their wedding share by @martha_weddings and cannot wait to show you all our favorite moments! @birdsofafeatherevents @cezanne.floral @goodmanfilmlab @kindredpresets @alisonheffington @juliewilmes @meganpettusfilms @theideaemporium

As the self-proclaimed “biggest fan of Father Of The Bride,” I can’t tell you how thrilling it is when you are asked to photograph a wedding at your client's home. Private estate weddings have an added layer of magic. Every moment holds more weight, and every backdrop in a photo holds more memories than just one. The weight sits differently. As an artist who strives to hold and capture moments with intention, it isn’t lost on me that at-home weddings have more complexity and beauty beyond the day at hand. This day was filled with memories and beautiful moments with loved ones, both present and passed. Tears of every kind and laughter of the same echoed through this day. It was an honor to hold space for every loved one on this day. What a gift it was to both leave and make space for old and new memories to exist in one frame. Here are a few frames from their unforgettable ceremony and a favorite portrait at the very end (you don’t want to miss that one!) Honorable mention to @alisonheffington for her golden retriever happy face creation prowess on slide 10.

Our September cover is here, 💙 featuring #OTMBride @jessicadelacruzpiechota and @gregpiechota's destination wedding (with an uninvited hail storm) 🌨️ in Lake Como. 🇮🇹 For the ceremony, Jessica found her dream lace dress at @MoniqueLhuillierbride on Melrose Place. "The second I tried on my dress, I immediately started to cry and knew it was the one; I did not want to take it off," she gushes. 🤍 "Fun Fact: I actually decided on my dress prior to finding our wedding venue, so once we decided on Italy, the dress made even more sense!" 

After being announced as officially married, the hailstorm ❄️ quickly rolled in and destroyed the glass marquee, where the beautiful reception had been set up. "It was so terrifying!" the bride exclaims. Hail had also hit Florence earlier that month and continued to arrive in Northern Italy throughout the summer—some pieces as big as tennis balls. 

Not ones to let anything derail their wedding day, the bride and groom were still ready to ring in their marriage with the biggest smiles on their faces. "I think just the overall fact that all our guests were soaking wet, in their very best outfits and dresses, hair dripping water, makeup ruined, and barefoot and yet still ready to party and celebrate regardless of what just happened made us so thankful for the people God has blessed to surround us with," Jessica reflects. 🪩

Lake Como. What a dream. And one we will NEVER forget! Jess and Greg, what an incredible celebration for one incredible love! What an honor that they are the September cover of @overthemoon ! ✨

Couldn’t have done this without the best team in the world! So grateful for these babes @jenneferwilson @alisonheffington

"I could not have felt more at peace, more grateful, and over the moon in my life," #OTMBride @jessicadelacruzpiechota says of her wedding ceremony at @villa_balbiano. 🇮🇹 "I gave myself a pep talk before the ceremony to remember to be so present in the moment and I did exactly that. I remember taking it all in and thinking this is better than any dream, fairytale, or movie." 🤍

Post-ceremony, Jessica went inside with two of her bridesmaids to bustle her dress, but an unexpected guest arrived outside. A severe hailstorm 🌨️ rolled in and destroyed the glass marquee, where the beautiful reception had been set up. "It was so hard to accept that a storm had just come in and destroyed our entire wedding venue and even more terrifying that our guests were hiding under tables and chairs to protect themselves after the marque had fallen down," Jessica shares. "Luckily everyone was safe and no one was hurt."
